verbose_text: There were no significant differences between the two groups of SMA mice treated with AAV9-STAS in their body weight (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY), the levels of viral mediated STAS mRNA overexpression in the spinal cord (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY), or the number of proprioceptive synapses on SMA motor neurons (aggregated data are shown in XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG) that could account for this observation.
